16 across state agencies and departments, and serving with an unwaveringly cheerful demeanor;
17 and
18 WHEREAS, a woman of determination and perseverance, she has also demonstrated
19 physical endurance through her participation in the Peachtree Road Race and several other
20 competitive races; and
21 WHEREAS, Talmadge James has served with honor and distinction, and her vision and
22 unyielding commitment to the Georgia House of Representatives will be sorely missed upon
23 the occasion of her retirement on March 1, 2025; and
24 WHEREAS, she is cherished by her colleagues under the Gold Dome, who count her
25 friendship as a special experience they will always treasure, and it is abundantly fitting and
26 proper that she be honored for her many contributions to this state.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize and commend Talmadge James for her two and a half
29 decades of efficient, effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service to the citizens of the
30 State of Georgia; congratulate her upon the grand occasion of her retirement; and extend
31 sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
34 Talmadge James.
